    <title><![CDATA[Waline Integration]]></title>
    <link>https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/integrations/waline</link>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/integrations/waline</guid>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="waline-integration">Waline Integration</h1><p>We support installing Waline to your blog.</p><p>Add <code>waline</code> property to your blog configuration <code>_config.yml</code>:</p><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre class="sourceCode yml"><code class="sourceCode yaml"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">waline</span><span class="kw">:</span></span><span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co"># Don&#39;t set `el` here.</span></span><span id="cb1-3"><a href="#cb1-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="fu">path</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> location.pathname</span></span><span id="cb1-4"><a href="#cb1-4" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="fu">serverURL</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&quot;&#39;https://example.com&#39;&quot;</span></span><span id="cb1-5"><a href="#cb1-5" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="fu">requiredMeta</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&quot;[&#39;nick&#39;, ...]&quot;</span></span></code></pre></div><p>All the sub-properties are the same as the script in <a href="https://waline.js.org/en/quick-start.html#html-references">HTML References - Quick Start | Waline</a> except <code>el</code>.</p><p>You should not set <code>el</code> property, it must match the EJS document.</p>]]></content>
    <pubDate>Sat, 2 Nov 2024 22:21:32 +0800</pubDate>
  </entry>
   
