  <entry>
    <title><![CDATA[Tags and Categories]]></title>
    <link>https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/tags-and-categories</link>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/tags-and-categories</guid>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="tags-and-categories">Tags and Categories</h1><p>Tags and categories features are enabled by default. But only part of them are available with zero-config. To make full use of them, follow the instructions:</p><h2 id="tags-and-categories-page">Tags and Categories Page</h2><p>Firstly, run these commands:</p><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre class="sourceCode sh"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true"></a>$ <span class="ex">hexo</span> new page <span class="st">&#39;tags&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true"></a>$ <span class="ex">hexo</span> new page <span class="st">&#39;categories&#39;</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Then, you should get two new files at <code>source/tags/index.md</code> and <code>source/categories/index.md</code>. Replace all of their content with the following:</p><p><code>source/tags/index.md</code></p><div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre class="sourceCode markdown"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span><span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="an">type:</span><span class="co"> tags</span></span><span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span></code></pre></div><p><code>source/categories/index.md</code></p><div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre class="sourceCode markdown"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span><span id="cb3-2"><a href="#cb3-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="an">type:</span><span class="co"> categories</span></span><span id="cb3-3"><a href="#cb3-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Done! Now, <code>/tags/</code> and <code>/categories/</code> pages will be generated correctly.</p>]]></content>
    <pubDate>Sat, 2 Nov 2024 22:21:32 +0800</pubDate>
  </entry>
   
  <entry>
    <title><![CDATA[Search]]></title>
    <link>https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/search</link>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/search</guid>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="search">Search</h1><p>Search features are enabled by default, but requires a few steps to make it available.</p><ol type="1"><li>Run</li></ol><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre class="sourceCode sh"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co"># [hexo-generator-search](https://github.com/wzpan/hexo-generator-search)</span></span><span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true"></a>$ <span class="ex">npm</span> install hexo-generator-search --save</span></code></pre></div><ol start="2" type="1"><li>Add these lines to blog configuration <code>_config.yml</code>:</li></ol><div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre class="sourceCode yml"><code class="sourceCode yaml"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">search</span><span class="kw">:</span></span><span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="fu">path</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> search.json</span></span><span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="fu">content</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="ch">false</span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="3" type="1"><li>Add new search page so that Hexo will generate it.</li></ol><div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre class="sourceCode sh"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true"></a>$ <span class="ex">hexo</span> new page <span class="st">&#39;search&#39;</span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="4" type="1"><li>Replace all its content with:</li></ol><div class="sourceCode" id="cb4"><pre class="sourceCode markdown"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb4-1"><a href="#cb4-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span><span id="cb4-2"><a href="#cb4-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="an">type:</span><span class="co"> search</span></span><span id="cb4-3"><a href="#cb4-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co">---</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Done! Your search page is ready at <code>/search/</code>.</p>]]></content>
    <pubDate>Sat, 2 Nov 2024 22:21:32 +0800</pubDate>
  </entry>
   
  <entry>
    <title><![CDATA[🌈 Rainbow Banner]]></title>
    <link>https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/rainbow-banner</link>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">https://pikapikapikaori.github.io/pikapikapi-blog/#/pages/hexo/themes/hexo-theme-cupertino/docs/features/rainbow-banner</guid>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="rainbow-banner">🌈 Rainbow Banner</h1><figure><img src="./img/rainbow-banner.png" alt="" /><figcaption>A screenshot of rainbow banner</figcaption></figure><p>Rainbow banner is enabled by default, and will only appear every June. You can customize it on your own to show your pride.</p><p>This is the default config:</p><div class="sourceCode" id="cb1"><pre class="sourceCode yaml"><code class="sourceCode yaml"><span id="cb1-1"><a href="#cb1-1" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co"># rainbow!</span></span><span id="cb1-2"><a href="#cb1-2" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">rainbow_banner</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="ch">true</span></span><span id="cb1-3"><a href="#cb1-3" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">rainbow_banner_colors</span><span class="kw">:</span></span><span id="cb1-4"><a href="#cb1-4" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#e50000&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-5"><a href="#cb1-5" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#ff8d00&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-6"><a href="#cb1-6" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#ffee00&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-7"><a href="#cb1-7" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#008121&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-8"><a href="#cb1-8" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#004cff&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-9"><a href="#cb1-9" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="at">  </span><span class="kw">-</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="st">&#39;#760188&#39;</span></span><span id="cb1-10"><a href="#cb1-10" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co"># choose from [auto, always]</span></span><span id="cb1-11"><a href="#cb1-11" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">rainbow_banner_shown</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> auto</span></span><span id="cb1-12"><a href="#cb1-12" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="co"># Pride Month by default</span></span><span id="cb1-13"><a href="#cb1-13" aria-hidden="true"></a><span class="fu">rainbow_banner_month</span><span class="kw">:</span><span class="at"> </span><span class="dv">6</span></span></code></pre></div><h2 id="rainbow_banner"><code>rainbow_banner</code></h2><p>A <code>boolean</code>, the main switch of this feature. When <code>false</code>, all the configurations below will make no effects.</p><h2 id="rainbow_banner_colors"><code>rainbow_banner_colors</code></h2><p>An <code>Array</code> of the colors of rainbow, from left to right, and has no amount limitation.</p><h2 id="rainbow_banner_shown"><code>rainbow_banner_shown</code></h2><p>Choose from <code>auto</code> and <code>always</code>. If <code>always</code>, the rainbow banner will be shown at anytime. If <code>auto</code>, the banner will only be shown in <code>rainbow_banner_month</code>.</p><h2 id="rainbow_banner_month"><code>rainbow_banner_month</code></h2><p>A <code>Number</code> between <code>[1, 12]</code>, the month when the rainbow banner will be shown, only works with <code>rainbow_banner_shown: auto</code>.</p>]]></content>
    <pubDate>Sat, 2 Nov 2024 22:21:32 +0800</pubDate>
  </entry>
   
